
         <h2>KDE4</h2>

         <p>We did our best trying to get KDE3 in the best shape possible for
         Etch.  We will keep packaging new minor releases (such as KDE 3.5.7),
         which will be available on unstable/testing repositories.</p>

         <p>According to <a
         href="http://techbase.kde.org/Schedules/KDE4/4.0_Release_Schedule">KDE
         4.0 release schedule</a>, KDE 4 should be released on October 23,
         2007, and we are already working on it.</p>

         <p>The kdelibs API is "soft-frozen", and the first alphas are getting
         out. While we are already packaging the software to detect and fix
         problems, the packages will not be uploaded to the experimental
         repository until KDE 4 reaches beta status (about end of June).
         We will also have Qt 4.3 then. We might also publish <a
         href="http://debian-live.alioth.debian.org/">Debian live-CD</a>'s
         with some of the beta releases.</p>

         <p>If you want to help in this task, you're welcome!</p>



